The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 16 (PTI): Data presented by the minister of personnel and training have shown that there is not a single officer from the scheduled caste category who has been appointed as a secretary at the Centre.           
	There are 88 secretaries, 66 additional secretaries, 249 joint secretaries and 471 directors in the government, the Lok Sabha was informed today.                   
	 Washington (PTI): Three Sikh musicians who had been denied permission to board a flight at a California airport about a year ago have received an apology and an undisclosed amount from the US Airways. Sikh organisations had called the incident a case of racial discrimination.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Four armed motorcyclists snatched Rs 1.55 crore from an elderly jeweller while he was waiting for his car outside home in Delhi on Wednesday morning. Puran Chand Goel, 62, was leaving for the bank to deposit the money.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): The army has ruled out the presence of the Taliban in Jammu and Kashmir and said it was capable of tackling any militant threat. There had been no increase in the number of foreign militants in the state, General Officer Commanding Lt Gen. Rameshwar Roy said at a programme organised to mark the 1971 victory.                  
	 New Delhi: The Centre has refused to lift the ban on pre-paid cellphone connections in Jammu and Kashmir. The Union home ministry has said the verification process has not been streamlined.
                                                                                                                                                    
